# Line-ending policy. Windows batch / PowerShell scripts MUST be CRLF — cmd.exe
# mis-parses LF-only .bat files (it drops the leading characters of each line, so
# `cd /d` becomes `/d`, `setlocal` becomes `tlocal`, etc., and the launcher breaks).
# Shell scripts MUST stay LF. git stores these normalized and checks them out with
# the right endings per-platform, so a clone on Windows always gets working .bat files.
*.bat   text eol=crlf
*.cmd   text eol=crlf
*.ps1   text eol=crlf
*.sh    text eol=lf
